team, here's the weekly update of what's delivered last week and what we aim to for the next.

Last week you saw us delivering:
- Billing - the whole stack has been released as a shadow feature, today we'll start switching on the service. this will be disruptive for the current ongoing rentals, as they'll require credits.
- incentives ramp up, the release of which has been a major success.
- CLI improvements

New and Ongoing work for this week
- Orchestrator - this will enable Basilica to offer services beyond rentals. Most of the team focus will be here this week.
- Extend the SDK and API for the same reason

Known defects & request that we'll try to deliver:
- Many instances do not have the right amount of storage that most of our users expect, we're considering different solutions to approach this.
- Mostly Grafana issues, seems the weights, availability and rented count is not reflecting the actual state
- Ability to add open ports on a rental after it's rented
- ability to restart/reset a rental without stopping the rental
- `root` username for the GPU node is still erroring, use a `basilica` user in your GPU nodes that is sudoer and has docker capabilities.

for anyone else, please make sure the basilica user has sudo and docker capabilities

Example of setup:

```
sudo useradd -m -s /bin/bash basilica
sudo usermod -aG sudo,docker basilica

echo "username ALL=(ALL) NOPASSWD:ALL" | sudo tee /etc/sudoers.d/basilica

sudo chmod 440 /etc/sudoers.d/basilica

sudo mkdir -p /home/basilica/.ssh
sudo chmod 700 /home/basilica/.ssh

echo "ssh-rsa ...miner's pub ssh key here.." | sudo tee /home/basilica/.ssh/authorized_keys

sudo chmod 600 /home/basilica/.ssh/authorized_keys

sudo chown -R basilica:basilica /home/basilica/.ssh


# make sure in the `/etc/ssh/sshd_config` you have this
PasswordAuthentication no
PubkeyAuthentication yes

# if you had to edit the above, then do this (it'll disconnect you you can reconnect again after)
sudo systemctl restart sshd
```
